<div class="p text-right font-secondary"><a href="table/table2-1758573218780519/" class="usa-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open in a new tab</a></div>
<div class="tw-foot p"><div class="fn" id="table-fn2-1758573218780519"><p>CTA: cuff tear arthropathy; DVT: deep venous thrombosis; ROH: removal
of hardware; RTSA: reverse total shoulder arthroplasty.</p></div></div></section><p>Patient-reported outcomes were available at over two-year follow-up in 21 of 26
surviving shoulders (80.1%, three reoperations, three deceased). The average
follow-up was 4.8 ± 2.0 (2.0–8.6) years. The average VAS (out of 100) was 7.1 ± 14.5
(0–50), SST was 8.3 ± 2.6 (3–12) yes responses, SANE was 80.2 ± 17.4 (40–100), and
ASES was 83.6 ± 14.1 (48.3–98.3) (<a href="#table3-1758573218780519" class="usa-link">Table 3</a>). </p>
